Normal NToV stat buffs: <br>
     PoTG/Marzin/Focus/Riotous/Blades/Divine Str<br>
     Shissar when I'm bored :)<br>
<br>
I've gotten up to 3705 hitpoints (not including when a bored shaman cast avatar on me :))<br>
<br>
As for needing, not needing AC/Mana/HP whatever, 90% of the time you won't need the full effort that all your gear does for you.  If you're going oom every fight or living with only 5hp remaining, odds are, you're doing something wrong.<br>
<br>
That being said, it should be a goal to raise all your stats, no matter what class you are.  For druids, yes, sta, ac and hps are important as secondary stats.  We have more base hp than the int-casters, and we get more raw ac.  As a trade off, our spells are 10x's as opt to aggro a mob (please, no speeches about controlling aggro - it happens no matter what at times).  We aggro by healing, by nuking, by debuffing.  We get a full range of &quot;hate you&quot; spells.<br>
<br>
Being able to live after a mob flurries you three times.<br>
That's cool.  :P <p><body link="#FFFFFF" vlink="#CCCCCC">

