Ever watched a shamman or chanter slow / tash etc a dragon 10 seconds into a fight? R I P. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uarkinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkinia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/22/01 1:37:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulotusflystewnicely.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lotusfly Stewnicely</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/23/01 3:56:27 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.prexus.com/ef/becky/snap.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: max AC/Hps.</span><hr size=1> In my opinion:<br>
<br>
&quot;As for needing, not needing AC/Mana/HP whatever, 90% of the time you won't need the full effort that all your gear does for you. If you're going oom every fight or living with only 5hp remaining, odds are, you're doing something wrong.&quot;<br>
<br>
You need to be at the mana cap; in nasty fights (North ToV usually) every drop of mana you can muster will be used up, then you're onto Mod Rods.  You *will* use everything that you have in your mana bar - the best equipped druids can cast more spells, obviously. :)<br>
<br>
Some Flowing Thought too, of course, is vital - 1 or 2 is practical to date, for +10/+20 mana per minute respectively.  Over a Vulak fight that's a non-trivial amount of mana.<br>
<br>
Whilst staying at the mana cap, you need your resists to be high for those times when you have to fight completely within an AE (Lord Feshlak, say).  <br>
<br>
Once you've maxed mana, and have comfortable resists, then beef up your HPs to withstand the AEs and mod rod drains.  Every less heal you have to throw on yourself is another heal which can go to your group, or an offensive spell on the mob.<br>
<br>
So, I disagree.  I think that your max mana and max HPs are *vital*.  Mana first, then HPs when it's maxed.  <br>
<br>
My resists don't tend to get a lot of use, as you can shield yourself from most AEs, but for the times when you cannot you need to have solid resists obviously (Feshlak, Dagarn, Zlexak if nuking). :)<br>
<br>
<br>
